1	# PostHog Astro (Static) Example Project
2	
3	Repository: https://github.com/PostHog/context-mill
4	Path: example-apps/astro-static
5	
6	---
7	
8	## README.md
9	
10	# PostHog Astro Static Example
11	
12	This is an [Astro](https://astro.build/) static site (SSG) example demonstrating PostHog integration with product analytics, session replay, and error tracking.
13	
14	It uses the PostHog web snippet directly and shows how to:
15	
16	- Initialize PostHog in a static Astro site using a reusable component
17	- Identify users after login
18	- Track custom events from pages
19	- Capture errors via `posthog.captureException()`
20	- Reset PostHog state on logout
21	
22	## Features
23	
24	- **Product analytics**: Track login and burrito consideration events
25	- **Session replay**: Enabled via PostHog snippet configuration
26	- **Error tracking**: Manual error capture sent to PostHog
27	- **Simple auth flow**: Demo login using localStorage
28	
29	## Getting started
30	
31	### 1. Install dependencies
32	
33	```bash
34	npm install
35	# or
36	pnpm install
37	```
38	
39	### 2. Configure environment variables
40	
41	Create a `.env` file in the project root:
42	
43	```bash
44	REDACTED
45	PUBLIC_POSTHOG_HOST=https://us.i.posthog.com
46	```
47	
48	Get your PostHog project token from your project settings in PostHog.
49	
50	### 3. Run the development server
51	
52	```bash
53	npm run dev
54	# or
55	pnpm dev
56	```
57	
58	Open `http://localhost:4321` in your browser.
59	
60	## Project structure
61	
62	```text
63	src/
64	  components/
65	    posthog.astro      # PostHog snippet with is:inline directive
66	    Header.astro       # Navigation + logout, calls posthog.reset()
67	  layouts/
68	    PostHogLayout.astro # Root layout that includes PostHog + Header
69	  lib/
70	    auth.ts            # Auth utilities (localStorage-based)
71	  pages/
72	    index.astro        # Login form, identifies user + captures 'user_logged_in'
73	    burrito.astro      # Burrito consideration demo, captures 'burrito_considered'
74	    profile.astro      # Profile + error tracking demo
75	  styles/
76	    global.css         # Global styles
77	```
78	
79	## Key integration points
80	
81	### PostHog initialization (`src/components/posthog.astro`)
82	
83	The PostHog snippet is included as an inline script to prevent Astro from processing it:
84	
85	```astro
86	<script is:inline>
87	  !function(t,e){...}(document,window.posthog||[]);
88	  posthog.init('<ph_project_token>', {
89	    api_host: 'https://us.i.posthog.com',
90	    defaults: '2026-01-30'
91	  })
92	</script>
93	```
94	
95	The `is:inline` directive is required to prevent TypeScript errors about `window.posthog`.
96	
97	### User identification (`src/pages/index.astro`)
98	
99	After a successful "login", the app identifies the user and captures a login event:
100	
101	```javascript
102	window.posthog?.identify(username);
103	window.posthog?.capture("user_logged_in");
104	```
105	
106	Identification happens **only on login**, all further requests will automatically use the same distinct ID.
107	
108	### Event tracking (`src/pages/burrito.astro`)
109	
110	The burrito page tracks a custom event when a user "considers" the burrito:
111	
112	```javascript
113	window.posthog?.capture("burrito_considered", {
114	  total_considerations: newCount,
115	  username: currentUser,
116	});
117	```
118	
119	This shows how to attach useful properties to events (e.g. counts, usernames).
120	
121	### Error tracking (`src/pages/profile.astro`)
122	
123	The profile page includes a button to trigger a test error:
124	
125	```javascript
126	try {
127	  throw new Error("Test error for PostHog error tracking");
128	} catch (err) {
129	  window.posthog?.captureException(err);
130	}
131	```
132	
133	### Logout and session reset (`src/components/Header.astro`)
134	
135	On logout, both the local auth state and PostHog state are cleared:
136	
137	```javascript
138	window.posthog?.capture("user_logged_out");
139	localStorage.removeItem("currentUser");
140	window.posthog?.reset();
141	```
142	
143	`posthog.reset()` clears the current distinct ID and session so the next login starts a fresh identity.
144	
